ain| military=Spanish Armed Forces| active=121200| reserve=15450| paramilitary=76750| population=48958159| references=<ref>[[#IISS2018|IISS 2018]], pp. 148</ref>}}\n{{Number of soldiers| country=Turkey| military=Turkish Armed Forces| active=355200| reserve=378700| paramilitary=156800| population=80845215| references=<ref>[[#IISS2018|IISS 2018]], pp. 156-157</ref>}}\n{{Number of soldiers| country=United Kingdom| military=British Armed Forces| active=146650| reserve=44250|paramilitary=0| population=64769452| references=<ref>[[#IISS2018|IISS 2018]], pp. 160-161</ref>}}\n{{Number of soldiers| country=United States| military=United States Armed Forces| active=1348400| reserve=857950| paramilitary=0|population=323995528| references=<ref>[[#IISS2018|IISS 2018]], pp. 46</ref>}}\n|}\n\n==Military expenditures==\nThe United States has a larger defense expenditure than all other members combined.<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/nato-and-the-united-states_us_5887844be4b08f5134b624ca Where Does The Relationship Between NATO And The U.S. Go From Here?], ''Huffington Post''</ref> Criticism of the organization by current US President [[Donald Trump]] caused various reactions from American and European political figures, ranging from ridicule to panic.<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/nato-allies-boost-defense-spending-in-the-wake-of-trump-criticism/2017/06/28/153584de-5a8c-11e7-aa69-3964a7d55207_story.html NATO allies boost defense spending in the wake of Trump criticism], ''The Washington Post''</ref><ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/donald-trump-nato-us-ambassador-ivo-daaalder-germany-funding-eastern-europe-security-poland-a7637611.html Former US ambassador to Nato in withering criticism of Donald Trump], ''The Independent''</ref><ref>[https://www.voanews.com/a/shaken-by-trump-s-criticism-of-nato-europe-mulls-building-own-military-force/3691549.html Shaken by Trump\u2019s Criticism of NATO, Europe Mulls Building Own Military Force], ''Voice Of America''</ref> [[Pew Research Center]]'s 2016 survey among its member states showed that while most countries viewed NATO positively, most NATO members preferred keeping their military spending the same. The response to whether their country should militarily aid another NATO country if it were to get into a serious military conflict with Russia was also mixed. Only in the US and Canada did more than 50% of the people answer that they should.<ref>[http://www.pewresearch.org/fact-tank/2016/07/06/support-for-nato-is-widespread-among-member-nations/ Support for NATO is widespread among member nations], ''Pew Research''</ref><ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-nato-survey-idUSKBN18J21J U.S. would defend NATO despite Trump's criticism, Europeans believe: study], ''Reuters''</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:right\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Member state\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Population{{efn|name=pop}}\n! rowspan=\"2\" | GDP (nominal){{efn|name=gdpn|[[Gross domestic product]] (nominal) data (in billions of US dollars) is based on an October 2019 issue of the ''World Economic Outlook'', which is published by the [[International Monetary Fund]].<ref name=\"GDP\">{{cite web |title=GDP, current prices |url=https://www.imf.org/external/datamapper/NGDPD@WEO/OEMDC/ADVEC/WEOWORLD |publisher=International Monetary Fund |accessdate=29 March 2020}}</ref>}}\n! colspan=\"3\" | Defence expenditure (US$){{efn|name=natodata|Defence expenditure and personnel data are based on a June 2019 press release from NATO.<ref name=\"NATO exp\">{{cite web |title=Defence Expenditure of NATO Countries (2012-2019) |url=https://www.nato.int/nato_static_fl2014/assets/pdf/pdf_2019_06/20190625_PR2019-069-EN.pdf |publisher=NATO |accessdate=30 March 2020 |date=25 June 2019}}</ref>}}\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Personnel{{efn|name=natodata}}\n|-\n! In millions\n! % [[real GDP]]\n! Per capita\n|- <!--        | {{flag|country}}         || Population  || GDP (nom) || Def exp || Ex % |