{"title_page": "Kamleshwar Patel", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{BLP sources|date=May 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Kamleshwar Patel\n| honorific_prefix    = \n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1974|05|01}}\n| birth_place         = [[Sidhi]]\n| residence           = [[Sidhi]]\n| nationality         = Indian\n| citizenship         = \n| office              = Member of the [[Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly]]\n| term_start          = [[2013 Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly election|2013]]\n| term_end            = \n| constituency        = [[Sihawal (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Sihawal]]\n| predecessor         = \n| education           = [[LLB]]<ref>{{cite web|title=MLA Profile|url=http://mpvidhansabha.nic.in/14thvs/2014_78.pdf|website=MP Vidhansabha|accessdate=16 May 2018}}</ref>\n| alma_mater          = \n| profession          = Politician\n| footnotes           = \n| party               = [[Indian National Congress]]\n| spouse              = Priti Patel\n| father              = Indrajeet Kumar\n| children            = \n}}\n'''Kamleshwar Patel''' is an Indian politician and a member of the [[Indian National Congress]] party.\n\nKamleshwar Patel was born on May 1, 1974 in [[Sidhi]].\nHe was elected from the Sihawal Vidhan Sabha constituency for the first time in the year 2013 and retained the seat in 2018 elections.\nKamleshwar Patel is minister of Panchayat and Rural Development in Madhya Pradesh government.\n\n==Political career==\n\u2022  '''Cabinet  Minister''' ('''''Panchayat and Rural Development)'''''<ref>{{Citation|title=Kamal Nath ministry|date=2020-03-25|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Kamal_Nath_ministry&oldid=947288976|work=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/28-legislators-take-oath-as-ministers-in-madhya-pradesh/articleshow/67243311.cms|title=Kamal Nath expands Cabinet; inducts 28 ministers, including 2 women|date=2018-12-25|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> from December 2018 to March 2020.\n\n\u2022 Became an '''MLA''' for the first time in [[2013 Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly election|2013]]<ref>{{cite web|title=MLA Information|url=http://myneta.info/mp2013/candidate.php?candidate_id=767|website=myneta.info|accessdate=16 May 2018}}</ref> to 2018 & 2018 reelected (''Sihawal -Sidhi)''\n\n\u2022 '''Vice Presiden'''t Madhya Pradesh Congress Committee.\n\n\u2022 '''Secretary All India Congress Committee''' (2017-18)\n\n\u2022 '''General Secretary''', Madhya Pradesh Congress Committee.\n\n\u2022 '''National Coordinator (Tour) Hon\u2019ble Rahul Gandhi''' - February 2009\n\n\u2022 '''General Secretary''' \u2013 All India Youth Congress from 13th August, 2005 to 17th January,\n\n2009.\n\n\u2022 '''Secretary''' \u2013 All India Youth Congress from 8th August 2003 \u2013 13th August 2005.\n\n\u2022 '''Chairperson''' \u2013 OBC Cell at All India Youth Congress from 5th February 2001 \u2013 8\n\nth August,\n\n2003.\n\n\u2022 '''Vice President''' \u2013 Madhya Pradesh State Youth Congress from 10th March, 1999 to 5th\n\nFebruary, 2001.\n\n\u2022 '''National Council Member''' \u2013 NSUI from 1996 to 1998.\n\n\u2022 '''General Secretary Madhya Pradesh''' \u2013 NSUI from 1992 \u2013 1994.\n\n\u2022 '''General Secretary Sidhi District''' \u2013 NSUI from 1989 \u2013 1990.\n\n==Political Views==\nHe supports Congress Party's Ideology\n\n'''Leadership Strengths'''\n\n\u2022 As sitting MLA exposed the ills of governance in the Assembly. ''Vigorously raised''\n\n''VYAPAM issue in Assembly.''\n\n\u2022 ''Led mass movements'' against the ill doings of BJP led M.P. Government.\n\n\u2022 Managing high profile political events and organizing issue-based protests.\n\n\u2022 Active in politics since school days from 1988 spanning nearly two decades.\n\n\u2022 Led the youths of Madhya Pradesh as student leader while serving many organizational\n\nposts in youth wings of Congress.\n\n\u2022 Nourished values among youths, established by the Congress Party.\n\n\u2022 Staged many public demonstrations, protest marches against anti-development and anti-\n\npeople policies.\n\n\u2022 Raised socio-economic and issues in state forcing policy changes.\n\n\u2022 Constant advocacy of masses on different issues of socio-economic importance.\n\n\u2022 Toured extensively in Uttar Pradesh, Chhattisgarh, Maharashtra, Mumbai, Rajasthan, New\n\nDelhi and Uttrakhand to give strategic leadership to youths.\n\n\u2022 Organized national level conventions to highlight policy engineered discrepancies pressing\n\nadministrative machineries to take corrective steps.\n\n\u2022 Well-versed with issues in higher and School education sectors as management head of a\n\nGroup of IT and Management Institutes.\n\n\u2022 I extensively toured all the Mandal and districts of Uttar Pradesh, Chhattisgarh,\n\nMaharashtra and Mumbai for the implementation and publicity of MNREGA and RTI.\n\n\u2022 Attended the state level seminars/workshops/symposia organized by or on behalf of AICC\n\nand State PCCs.\n\n\u2022 Led anti-farmer protest rally participated by 10,000 people.\n\n\u2022 Designed Nari Samman Yatra as part of Parivartan Yatra \u2013 April 5, 2013.\n\n\u2022 Participated in national level training conducted by Youth Congress and NSUI at New\n\nDelhi.\n\n\u2022 Led Anti Corruption Rallies frequently.\n\n'''Social Enterprise -'''\n\n\u2022 Organized sports events like interstate Kabaddi tournament, football, cricket tournaments.\n\n\u2022 Organized awareness campaigns on health issues and led door-to-door counseling sessions\n\non diseases like malaria, cholera.\n\n\u2022 Designed and launched awareness rallies educating locals on social evils like dowry,\n\nalcoholism.\n\n\u2022 Organized block level orientation training programs for Congress volunteers.\n\n\u2022 Participation in OBC youth conferences, organized community social gatherings on social\n\ncauses.\n\n\u2022 Organized educational activities like Talent Hunt competition as member of management\n\ncommittee of Patel Group of Institutions with headquarters at Bhopal and Indore.\n\n'''Electoral Management \u2013'''\n\n\u2022 Managed electioneering in Lok Sabha and Assembly Elections.\n\n\u2022 Devised issued based election campaigns.\n\n\u2022 Actively participated in state level election management exercises.\n\n\u2022 Pro-active participation in Panchayat Raj and Civic Body elections.\n\n'''Leadership Guidance'''\n\nGrown under the tutelage of my father '''Shri Indrajit Kumar''' \u2013 a committed sentinel of the\n\nCongress Party and MLA from Sidhi \u2013 74 (Madhya Pradesh).\n\n'''Credits'''\n\n\u2022 Working closely with MPCC in launching protests against BJP led- MP Government.\n\n\u2022 Raised many issues specially crimes against women, BJP political leadership-sponsored\n\ncorruption, worsening law and order in the constituent assembly areas desired by MPCC.\n\n\u2022 Led protest marches in favour of SC/ST/OBC to protect their rights and entitlements.\n\n\u2022 Maintained inflow of inputs to MPCC in respect of feedback and firm actions and planning\n\nstrategies.\n\n\u2022 Successive State Governments accelerated the process of reforms in primary education\n\nsector due to impressive demands.\n\n\u2022 Governments agreed to raise upper age limit for government jobs and give reservation to\n\nwomen.\n\n\u2022 Conducted Educative Tours.\n\n\u2022 '''Dandi Yatra''' \u2013 I was among the 78 members who attend the Dandi Yatra on the occasion\n\nof 75th Anniversary of Dandi Yatra from Sabarmati to Dandi 500 Kms. Padyatra 25 days.\n\n\u2022 Led public protests and agitations.\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is married to Mrs. Priti Patel and has one son and one daughter.\n\n==Legal Matters==\nThe MP High Court had ordered the police to order an FIR against Kamleshwar Patel for forgery in the election form.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Editorial|first1=Team|title=Court orders FIR against Sihawal MLA Kamleshwar Patel|url=https://naidunia.jagran.com/madhya-pradesh/jabalpur-court-orders-fir-against-shivlal-mla-kamleshwar-patel-1171025|accessdate=16 May 2018|agency=Naidunia|publisher=naidunia.jagran.com|date=25 May 2017}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kale|first1=Makarand|title=FIR lodged against Congress MLA on the orders of the High Court|url=https://hindi.news18.com/madhya-pradesh/bhopal-news-fir-lodged-against-congress-mla-kamleshwar-patel-at-bhopal-1018367.html|accessdate=16 May 2018|agency=ETV MP/Chhattisgarh|publisher=hindi.news18.com|date=16 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly]]\n*[[2013 Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly election]]\n*[[Sihawal (Vidhan Sabha constituency)]]\n*[[Indian National Congress]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Facebook|100014815447181}}\n\n[https://www.instagram.com/patel_kamleshwar/ Kamleshwar Patel on Instagram] \n{{Indian National Congress}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Patel, Kamleshwar}}\n[[Category:Madhya Pradesh MLAs 2013\u20132018]]\n[[Category:Madhya Pradesh MLAs 2018\u2013]]\n[[Category:Indian National Congress politicians from Madhya Pradesh]][[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{INC-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{BLP sources|date=May 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Kamleshwar Patel\n| honorific_prefix    = \n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1974|05|01}}\n| birth_place         = [[Sidhi]]\n| residence           = [[Sidhi]]\n| nationality         = Indian\n| citizenship         = \n| office              = Member of the [[Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly]]\n| term_start          = [[2013 Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly election|2013]]\n| term_end            = \n| constituency        = [[Sihawal (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Sihawal]]\n| predecessor         = \n| education           = [[LLB]]<ref>{{cite web|title=MLA Profile|url=http://mpvidhansabha.nic.in/14thvs/2014_78.pdf|website=MP Vidhansabha|accessdate=16 May 2018}}</ref>\n| alma_mater          = \n| profession          = Politician\n| footnotes           = \n| party               = [[Indian National Congress]]\n| spouse              = Priti Patel\n| father              = Indrajeet Kumar\n| children            = \n}}\n'''Kamleshwar Patel''' is an Indian politician and a member of the [[Indian National Congress]] party.\n\nKamleshwar Patel was born on May 1, 1974 in [[Sidhi]].\nHe was elected from the Sihawal Vidhan Sabha constituency for the first time in the year 2013 and retained the seat in 2018 elections.\nKamleshwar Patel is minister of Panchayat and Rural Development in Madhya Pradesh government.\n\n==Political career==\n\u2022 He have been '''Cabinet  Minister''' ('''''Panchayat and Rural Development)'''''<ref>{{Citation|title=Kamal Nath ministry|date=2020-03-25|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Kamal_Nath_ministry&oldid=947288976|work=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/28-legislators-take-oath-as-ministers-in-madhya-pradesh/articleshow/67243311.cms|title=Kamal Nath expands Cabinet; inducts 28 ministers, including 2 women|date=2018-12-25|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> from December 2018 to March 2020.\n\n\u2022 He became an '''MLA''' for the first time in [[2013 Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly election|2013]]<ref>{{cite web|title=MLA Information|url=http://myneta.info/mp2013/candidate.php?candidate_id=767|website=myneta.info|accessdate=16 May 2018}}</ref> to 2018 & 2018 reelected (''Sihawal -Sidhi)''\n\n\u2022 '''Vice Presiden'''t Madhya Pradesh Congress Committee.\n\n\u2022 '''Secretary All India Congress Committee''' (2017-18)\n\n\u2022 '''General Secretary''', Madhya Pradesh Congress Committee.\n\n\u2022 '''National Coordinator (Tour) Hon\u2019ble Rahul Gandhi''' - February 2009\n\n\u2022 '''General Secretary''' \u2013 All India Youth Congress from 13th August, 2005 to 17th January,\n\n2009.\n\n\u2022 '''Secretary''' \u2013 All India Youth Congress from 8th August 2003 \u2013 13th August 2005.\n\n\u2022 '''Chairperson''' \u2013 OBC Cell at All India Youth Congress from 5th February 2001 \u2013 8\n\nth August,\n\n2003.\n\n\u2022 '''Vice President''' \u2013 Madhya Pradesh State Youth Congress from 10th March, 1999 to 5th\n\nFebruary, 2001.\n\n\u2022 '''National Council Member''' \u2013 NSUI from 1996 to 1998.\n\n\u2022 '''General Secretary Madhya Pradesh''' \u2013 NSUI from 1992 \u2013 1994.\n\n\u2022 '''General Secretary Sidhi District''' \u2013 NSUI from 1989 \u2013 1990.\n\n==Political Views==\nHe supports Congress Party's Ideology\n\n'''Leadership Strengths'''\n\n\u2022 As sitting MLA exposed the ills of governance in the Assembly. ''Vigorously raised''\n\n''VYAPAM issue in Assembly.''\n\n\u2022 ''Led mass movements'' against the ill doings of BJP led M.P. Government.\n\n\u2022 Managing high profile political events and organizing issue-based protests.\n\n\u2022 Active in politics since school days from 1988 spanning nearly two decades.\n\n\u2022 Led the youths of Madhya Pradesh as student leader while serving many organizational\n\nposts in youth wings of Congress.\n\n\u2022 Nourished values among youths, established by the Congress Party.\n\n\u2022 Staged many public demonstrations, protest marches against anti-development and anti-\n\npeople policies.\n\n\u2022 Raised socio-economic and issues in state forcing policy changes.\n\n\u2022 Constant advocacy of masses on different issues of socio-economic importance.\n\n\u2022 Toured extensively in Uttar Pradesh, Chhattisgarh, Maharashtra, Mumbai, Rajasthan, New\n\nDelhi and Uttrakhand to give strategic leadership to youths.\n\n\u2022 Organized national level conventions to highlight policy engineered discrepancies pressing\n\nadministrative machineries to take corrective steps.\n\n\u2022 Well-versed with issues in higher and School education sectors as management head of a\n\nGroup of IT and Management Institutes.\n\n\u2022 I extensively toured all the Mandal and districts of Uttar Pradesh, Chhattisgarh,\n\nMaharashtra and Mumbai for the implementation and publicity of MNREGA and RTI.\n\n\u2022 Attended the state level seminars/workshops/symposia organized by or on behalf of AICC\n\nand State PCCs.\n\n\u2022 Led anti-farmer protest rally participated by 10,000 people.\n\n\u2022 Designed Nari Samman Yatra as part of Parivartan Yatra \u2013 April 5, 2013.\n\n\u2022 Participated in national level training conducted by Youth Congress and NSUI at New\n\nDelhi.\n\n\u2022 Led Anti Corruption Rallies frequently.\n\n'''Social Enterprise -'''\n\n\u2022 Organized sports events like interstate Kabaddi tournament, football, cricket tournaments.\n\n\u2022 Organized awareness campaigns on health issues and led door-to-door counseling sessions\n\non diseases like malaria, cholera.\n\n\u2022 Designed and launched awareness rallies educating locals on social evils like dowry,\n\nalcoholism.\n\n\u2022 Organized block level orientation training programs for Congress volunteers.\n\n\u2022 Participation in OBC youth conferences, organized community social gatherings on social\n\ncauses.\n\n\u2022 Organized educational activities like Talent Hunt competition as member of management\n\ncommittee of Patel Group of Institutions with headquarters at Bhopal and Indore.\n\n'''Electoral Management \u2013'''\n\n\u2022 Managed electioneering in Lok Sabha and Assembly Elections.\n\n\u2022 Devised issued based election campaigns.\n\n\u2022 Actively participated in state level election management exercises.\n\n\u2022 Pro-active participation in Panchayat Raj and Civic Body elections.\n\n'''Leadership Guidance'''\n\nGrown under the tutelage of my father '''Shri Indrajit Kumar''' \u2013 a committed sentinel of the\n\nCongress Party and MLA from Sidhi \u2013 74 (Madhya Pradesh).\n\n'''Credits'''\n\n\u2022 Working closely with MPCC in launching protests against BJP led- MP Government.\n\n\u2022 Raised many issues specially crimes against women, BJP political leadership-sponsored\n\ncorruption, worsening law and order in the constituent assembly areas desired by MPCC.\n\n\u2022 Led protest marches in favour of SC/ST/OBC to protect their rights and entitlements.\n\n\u2022 Maintained inflow of inputs to MPCC in respect of feedback and firm actions and planning\n\nstrategies.\n\n\u2022 Successive State Governments accelerated the process of reforms in primary education\n\nsector due to impressive demands.\n\n\u2022 Governments agreed to raise upper age limit for government jobs and give reservation to\n\nwomen.\n\n\u2022 Conducted Educative Tours.\n\n\u2022 '''Dandi Yatra''' \u2013 I was among the 78 members who attend the Dandi Yatra on the occasion\n\nof 75th Anniversary of Dandi Yatra from Sabarmati to Dandi 500 Kms. Padyatra 25 days.\n\n\u2022 Led public protests and agitations.\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is married to Mrs. Priti Patel and has one son and one daughter.\n\n==Legal Matters==\nThe MP High Court had ordered the police to order an FIR against Kamleshwar Patel for forgery in the election form.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Editorial|first1=Team|title=Court orders FIR against Sihawal MLA Kamleshwar Patel|url=https://naidunia.jagran.com/madhya-pradesh/jabalpur-court-orders-fir-against-shivlal-mla-kamleshwar-patel-1171025|accessdate=16 May 2018|agency=Naidunia|publisher=naidunia.jagran.com|date=25 May 2017}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kale|first1=Makarand|title=FIR lodged against Congress MLA on the orders of the High Court|url=https://hindi.news18.com/madhya-pradesh/bhopal-news-fir-lodged-against-congress-mla-kamleshwar-patel-at-bhopal-1018367.html|accessdate=16 May 2018|agency=ETV MP/Chhattisgarh|publisher=hindi.news18.com|date=16 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly]]\n*[[2013 Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly election]]\n*[[Sihawal (Vidhan Sabha constituency)]]\n*[[Indian National Congress]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Facebook|100014815447181}}\n\n[https://www.instagram.com/patel_kamleshwar/ Kamleshwar Patel on Instagram] \n{{Indian National Congress}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Patel, Kamleshwar}}\n[[Category:Madhya Pradesh MLAs 2013\u20132018]]\n[[Category:Madhya Pradesh MLAs 2018\u2013]]\n[[Category:Indian National Congress politicians from Madhya Pradesh]][[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{INC-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "DigitalmansiT", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kamleshwar_Patel"}
